# KenTender — DocType controller class names (Frappe)

## Rule

Frappe loads the controller with:

`classname = doctype.replace(" ", "").replace("-", "")`

It is **not** “PascalCase each word.” Any short word in the desk title keeps its **original casing** when spaces are removed.

## Examples

| Desk name (`name` in JSON) | Required Python class |
| -------------------------- | --------------------- |
| `Evaluation Session` | `EvaluationSession` |
| `Conflict of Interest Declaration` | `ConflictofInterestDeclaration` (note lowercase **`o`** in `of`) |
| `Bid Opening Register` | `BidOpeningRegister` |

Wrong class → `get_controller` fails → during **`bench migrate`**, `remove_orphan_doctypes()` treats **`ImportError`** as an orphan and **deletes** the DocType row (symptoms: DocType vanishes, or misleading `frappe.core.doctype…` errors after deletion).

## Before merge

After adding or renaming a DocType controller, verify on a site:

`bench --site <site> console` → `frappe.clear_cache(); from frappe.model.base_document import get_controller; get_controller("Your DocType Name")`

If this raises `ImportError`, fix the **class name** in `your_doctype.py` to match the algorithm above (do not rename the desk title just to satisfy naming unless product agrees).
